boxºDisplayMgrºFile: DisplayMgr.c,12     Owner: Ian Hendry     Project: SuperMarioProjºToolboxºDisplayMgrºFile: DisplayMgr.make,5     Owner: Ian Hendry     Project: SuperMarioProjºToolboxºDisplayMgrºFile: DisplayMgrUtils.c,6     Owner: Ian Hendry     Project: SuperMarioProjºToolboxºDisplayMgrºRadar bug: #1101633,1098397,1101795,1101636,1102280> Release notes for this change:Fixed a number of compatibility bugs (1101633,1098397,1101795,1101636,1102280).I investigated a number of strategies for compatibility when the main displaychanged to a different monitor.  The problem was that there were alway incompatibilitieswith some applications and/or performance penalties.New Implementation:Exchange the contents the old main device and the new main device so that cached handlesstill behave correctly.  There is no performance penalty and (so far) no applicationincompatibilities beyond those introduced by the change in size.  I dicussed all thesesolutions with Kon Othmer and we both feel this is the base strategy.  The only problemis that this implementation breaks the connection between a phsyical monitor and itsgDevice.Rejected implementations:ÊÊ(1) changing the lo-mem MainDevice field (apps cache this value),ÊÊ(2) introducing a dummy device in the device list that MainDevice points to andshadowing and disabling the real main device such that caching MainDevice handle works(some apps had problems and performance suffered because QD always take the multidevicecase, and boot code assumes that all devices in the device list are active screen devicesand therefore ÔscrnÕ resources are invalid if it finds an extra device),ÊÊ(3) introducing a dummy device BEFORE the device list and pointed MainDevice at it.Fixed the boot problems and the performance hit, but broke applications that assumeMainDevice is in device list (including MicroSoft Excel).Added compatibility model.  Conditionally compiled fixes in a separate file with someguildlines for making sure these fixes can be turned off.  The CloseView compatilbilityfix is the only one in use.WARNING:WARNING:  As of this check in, you must use either Pre-Display Manager Monitors CP orWARNING:  Psychic TV A4 Monitors CP.  The API changed slightly to clean up the interfaceWARNING:  and intermediate versions will crash.WARNING:> What was tested:Built and tested extension with Reality sources.  Margarita regressed most of theexisting bugs and things seemed to work.  I updated SuperMario from reality and built andtested resolution flipping and new version of monitors on PDM.  Everything seems fine.----------------------------------------------------------¥----------------------------------------------------------